This course introduces different qualitative research and data analysis methods used in economics and social sciences. An overview of basic principles of carrying out interviews, surveys, observations, case studies etc. will be given. Relationships between research object, research problems and aims, theoretical standpoints and research methods are introduced. Topics of research planning, data collection, data analysis and presenting of results in qualitative research will be covered. Course ends with an introduction of different quantitative and qualitative data analysis methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course enables to get knowledge of different methods used in data gathering and analysis in qualitative and quantitative research in economics and social sciences and the main principles and problems of research methodology. Enables to develop students' analytical skills, critical thinking and is meant for improving the level of students' master projects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knowledge of the nature of scientific research and specificity of economic and business research; research strategies, design of research and steps of research process. Knowledge of different data gathering and analysing methods. Skills to apply different data gathering methods (interviews, surveys, case studies, etc.). Skills to systematise and prepare data for data analysis and carry out the data analysis. Skills to interpret and generalise the results of data analysis and skills to present the research results.
